<subSubSection id="44E57D94C8AFEC20084DB446C34B8C07" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A265721A7166FC29C69EDDA7654C0E8D" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="944B4AF2736EE2FC40AEC1D135A26711" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
The name 
<emphasis id="1F60F411DDDC32AC24BB4C07EEA8E276" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">brevi</emphasis>
(short) + 
<emphasis id="A7C4D6A457D1619FD4E5F376B2D114CF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">ceps</emphasis>
(head) was chosen because of the particularly short and wide head of this species, even within the 
<taxonomicName id="B6D45B62361A940355630FF7B5E7CC1F" authority="Warncke, 1968" authorityName="Warncke" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Poliandrena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Poliandrena" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9BAE5381AA3C9EDC0758B3BB4A7C1C9D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Poliandrena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
